1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,753
<i>You killed Louisa! You monster!</i>

2
00:00:03,837 --> 00:00:06,297
<i>We all suffered because of you!</i>

3
00:00:08,258 --> 00:00:11,886
<i>You used us to cover your sins!</i>

4
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:12,971
<i>You monster!</i>

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:14,556
- [grunts]
<i>- Ah!</i>

6
00:00:14,639 --> 00:00:15,807
<i>- Ah!</i>
- [gunshot]

7
00:00:16,391 --> 00:00:20,520
<i>Finally, you're all complete.</i>

8
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:23,440
<i>Edong, we already know the truth.</i>

9
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:26,067
<i>We can finally clear your name.</i>

10
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:27,694
<i>It's too late.</i>

11
00:00:28,319 --> 00:00:30,572
<i>You all destroyed my family!</i>

12
00:00:30,655 --> 00:00:31,698
<i>Edong, stop!</i>

13
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:36,327
[dramatic music playing]

14
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:49,758
[sinister music playing]

15
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:51,551
- Please stop.
- [whimpers]

16
00:00:51,634 --> 00:00:56,514
[dramatic music playing]

17
00:00:57,599 --> 00:00:58,725
[gunshot]

18
00:01:00,101 --> 00:01:01,895
- [gun thuds]
- Lucas! Edong!

19
00:01:01,978 --> 00:01:04,773
[screaming, whimpering]

20
00:01:05,774 --> 00:01:06,649
Edong!

21
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:08,359
[sniffles]

22
00:01:08,443 --> 00:01:10,528
[music become tense]

23
00:01:10,612 --> 00:01:11,738
[women sobbing]

24
00:01:11,821 --> 00:01:13,323
Put the gun down, Edong!

25
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:17,410
[women sobbing shakily, whimpering]

26
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:20,038
[sobs] Put the gun down.

27
00:01:20,955 --> 00:01:23,166
[somber music playing]

28
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:25,877
[Lucas] I'm begging you! Put the gun down!

29
00:01:26,628 --> 00:01:28,004
Put it down!

30
00:01:28,087 --> 00:01:32,467
- [sobbing continues]
- [somber music continues]

31
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:33,927
- Please.
- Put it down.

32
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:35,220
[breathes sharply]

33
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:44,979
- [sobbing continues]
- [somber music continues]

34
00:01:46,523 --> 00:01:47,649
[sniffles]

35
00:01:58,493 --> 00:01:59,786
[Lucas sniffles]

36
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:01,621
Are you going to shoot me, Lucas?

37
00:02:03,373 --> 00:02:04,749
I don't want to, Edong.

38
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:08,419
[Lucas sniffling]

39
00:02:08,503 --> 00:02:10,088
I'm begging you.

40
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:12,841
[sobs shakily] Don't…

41
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:14,717
[mouths] Don't… [sobs]

42
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,803
Don't force me to do it.

43
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:19,097
[cries softly]

44
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:20,723
I'm almost done, Lucas.

45
00:02:24,561 --> 00:02:29,107
[breathes sharply]
Allow me to finish my mission!

46
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:31,693
Please, no, Edong. I'm begging you.

47
00:02:33,027 --> 00:02:34,070
[sniffles]

48
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,905
I'm begging you.

49
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:37,198
[cries]

50
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:38,783
- [Edong] Do you think…
- [music fades]

51
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:42,871
[sobs] …Mama would be happy if she saw me?

52
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:44,831
- [crying shakily]
- [melancholic music playing]

53
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:47,083
- Don't do it, please.
- [Edong sobs shakily]

54
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:50,420
[sobbing shakily]

55
00:02:50,503 --> 00:02:52,505
Would she give me a hug?

56
00:02:52,589 --> 00:02:57,552
[melancholic music continues]

57
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:03,141
- [music becomes sinister]
- No! Edong, please stop! Please!

58
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:04,434
[breathes sharply]

59
00:03:04,517 --> 00:03:05,768
Stop! [grunts]

60
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:08,646
- [both grunting loudly]
- [tense music playing]

61
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,565
- [gun thuds]
- [both grunt]

62
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:13,443
- [grunts]
- [breathes sharply]

63
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:15,111
- Lucas!
- [Edong gasps]

64
00:03:15,194 --> 00:03:16,696
- [grunts]
- [breathes sharply]

65
00:03:16,779 --> 00:03:22,744
[tense music swells]

66
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:37,508
[music turns suspenseful]

67
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:41,554
[both grunt loudly]

68
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:42,889
Ah! Edong!

69
00:03:42,972 --> 00:03:45,892
[both grunting]

70
00:03:45,975 --> 00:03:48,102
- [Lucas] ah!
- [Edong grunts]

71
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:56,319
- [poignant music playing]
- [high-pitched ringing]

72
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:09,457
[poignant music continues]

73
00:04:11,709 --> 00:04:17,674
- [heart pounding fast]
- [poignant music intensifies]

74
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:21,469
[gunshot]

75
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:24,389
[thuds]

76
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:30,395
[somber music playing]

77
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:53,251
[somber music continues]

78
00:04:54,043 --> 00:04:58,631
- [Lucas sobbing]
- [Edong breathing weakly]

79
00:04:58,715 --> 00:05:00,049
Edong, Edong…

80
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:04,512
- [Edong breathes weakly]
- [sobbing continues]

81
00:05:06,014 --> 00:05:08,975
- [Lucas whimpers]
- [Edong breathes weakly]

82
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:12,687
- [Lucas sniffles, sobbing]
- [Edong breathing weakly]

83
00:05:12,770 --> 00:05:18,526
- [somber music continues]
- [Lucas sobbing softly]

84
00:05:18,609 --> 00:05:19,485
[Lucas sniffles]

85
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:22,905
[sobbing continues]

86
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:25,408
I never dreamed of this.

87
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:28,244
[sobbing softly, sniffles]

88
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:34,417
[somber music continues]

89
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,878
[agonizing scream]

90
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,133
- [gasps loudly]
- [sobs]

91
00:05:46,137 --> 00:05:51,434
[sorrowful music playing]

92
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:16,292
[sorrowful music continues]

93
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:23,716
[music fades]

94
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:28,763
- [suspenseful music playing]
- "CASE FILE: THE PHILIPPINES"

95
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:30,264
- [music fades]
- [electricity zapping]

96
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:34,644
"The time of fear and
danger is over, here in Amurao."

97
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:38,523
These are the words
that a police officer proudly uttered

98
00:06:38,606 --> 00:06:42,026
after the fugitive
PDL Edong Santiago was killed

99
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:46,030
when he was shot by
his own brother Lucas Santiago.

100
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:49,367
After this,
the police located his hideout,

101
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:55,289
where a cellphone
containing a video of his brutal murder

102
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:58,126
of TV host Anton Montenegro was found.

103
00:06:58,209 --> 00:07:03,381
[unsettling music playing]

104
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:12,807
But almost at the same
time as Santiago's death,

105
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:15,309
a painful truth was revealed.

106
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:17,687
<i>Louisa Soria's murder</i>

107
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:21,149
<i>which was attributed to him 11 years ago,</i>

108
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:24,819
<i>a crime that has</i>
<i>sentenced him to life imprisonment,</i>

109
00:07:24,902 --> 00:07:26,779
<i>was something he did not commit.</i>

110
00:07:27,488 --> 00:07:31,617
<i>The real culprit was</i>
<i>a man named Edward Mayo.</i>

111
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:33,202
<i>An admirable husband.</i>

112
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:35,246
<i>A respected church volunteer.</i>

113
00:07:35,329 --> 00:07:40,334
<i>One of Santiago's accusers</i>
<i>considered him to be her second father.</i>

114
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:44,088
<i>Mayo killed Soria when she discovered</i>

115
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:46,382
<i>that he was a serial child predator.</i>

116
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:48,759
<i>Based on the investigation</i>
<i>of the NLEA Police,</i>

117
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:51,220
<i>his victims consist</i>
<i>of approximately 20 girls</i>

118
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:54,599
<i>between the ages of four and seven.</i>

119
00:07:55,475 --> 00:08:00,021
<i>While people applauded the officer</i>
<i>who caught and prosecuted an innocent man,</i>

120
00:08:00,104 --> 00:08:03,691
<i>the real criminal was</i>
<i>given a microphone in the church</i>

121
00:08:03,774 --> 00:08:06,903
<i>and trust to get</i>
<i>close to his next victims.</i>

122
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:11,282
<i>The cases of Santiago and Mayo</i>

123
00:08:11,365 --> 00:08:14,118
<i>is a severe blow to our judiciary,</i>

124
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:16,454
<i>a system that is supposed to protect,</i>

125
00:08:16,537 --> 00:08:18,706
<i>but often fails to do so.</i>

126
00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:21,584
<i>This is especially true for</i>
<i>those who don't have money or power.</i>

127
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:24,462
If the people in
power don't deal with this,

128
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:27,465
this won't be the last
Edong Santiago who will fall victim

129
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:29,592
of an unjust system.

130
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:33,638
Edong Santiago
will never get his life back.

131
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:37,141
The same goes for the children
who were abused and killed by Edward Mayo.

132
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:40,186
However, this story can be corrected.

133
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:42,396
In the face of these tragedies,

134
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,565
the question of the people is…

135
00:08:44,649 --> 00:08:47,818
Will the system
continue to help other criminals?

136
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:50,279
Who else will be buried next?

137
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:54,325
<i>Is the era of</i>
<i>fear and danger coming to end</i>

138
00:08:54,408 --> 00:08:56,494
<i>here in our country?</i>

139
00:08:56,577 --> 00:08:59,997
[morose music playing, fades]

140
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:05,044
[theme music playing]

141
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:08,464
[Erica] <i>Each of us is more</i>
<i>than the worst thing we've ever done.</i>

142
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:13,928
It took me a long time
to understand something important.

143
00:09:15,304 --> 00:09:18,140
There are times when we can't avoid

144
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:20,101
the inaction of justice.

145
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:22,728
However…

146
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:27,066
we should not stop protesting.

147
00:09:28,484 --> 00:09:29,860
Like me…

148
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:31,404
we will fail.

149
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:33,531
Spectacularly.

150
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:36,284
We won't always be brave.

151
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,329
We won't always win.

152
00:09:41,497 --> 00:09:43,708
But the work doesn't end when we fail.

153
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:45,501
In fact,

154
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:48,588
that is exactly when the work begins.

155
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:52,133
You're not just here to memorize the law.

156
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:55,678
You're here to make sure that justice

157
00:09:55,761 --> 00:09:58,764
doesn't arrive too late for someone else.

158
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:01,100
Like it did for Louisa…

159
00:10:01,183 --> 00:10:03,311
[pensive music playing]

160
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:04,687
…and for Edong.

161
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:08,274
Every day is an opportunity…

162
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:12,028
for us to fix what's
wrong with our society.

163
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:15,406
Every day is an opportunity

164
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:19,619
to change the tragedies and stories…

165
00:10:21,329 --> 00:10:22,913
not only for us,

166
00:10:23,706 --> 00:10:26,250
but also for the people around us.

167
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:30,880
Be the lawyer that fights for truth…

168
00:10:31,505 --> 00:10:33,174
even when it's inconvenient.

169
00:10:34,091 --> 00:10:35,885
Even when it's uncomfortable.

170
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:39,513
Even when the world
calls you a fool for trying.

171
00:10:40,806 --> 00:10:42,141
Because, sometimes…

172
00:10:42,808 --> 00:10:48,022
a person may just one
lawyer away from gaining justice.

173
00:10:49,273 --> 00:10:51,776
And if you're that lawyer…

174
00:10:52,276 --> 00:10:55,571
then that person is very, very lucky.

175
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:57,990
[pensive music continues]

176
00:10:58,074 --> 00:11:02,703
[applause]

177
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:07,124
[music fades]

178
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:11,128
[Lucas] <i>You must be together with Mom now?</i>

179
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:12,630
[somber music playing]

180
00:11:12,713 --> 00:11:14,215
<i>I'm sure that…</i>

181
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:17,676
<i>she hugged you tightly</i>
<i>as soon as she saw you.</i>

182
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,929
[somber music continues]

183
00:11:20,012 --> 00:11:22,681
I'm sure she missed you so much.

184
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:26,185
You must've proven that…

185
00:11:26,894 --> 00:11:28,354
she loves you very much.

186
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:31,524
I told you so.

187
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:35,236
No matter what you've done,
I won't turn my back on you.

188
00:11:35,319 --> 00:11:39,698
[somber music continues]

189
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,033
Brother…

190
00:11:41,117 --> 00:11:42,201
I hope…

191
00:11:43,577 --> 00:11:47,540
that you've finally found
the peace that the world denied you.

192
00:11:48,749 --> 00:11:50,251
I'd like to ask for your forgiveness.

193
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:54,171
I'm sorry if I couldn't give
you the life you've dreamed of.

194
00:11:54,255 --> 00:11:56,257
[somber music continues]

195
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:58,134
But I promise you, Brother…

196
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:01,220
I will try to live a life that…

197
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:04,056
you and Mama can be proud of.

198
00:12:05,182 --> 00:12:06,934
So that when see each other again…

199
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:09,937
you'll be smiling.

200
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:13,774
[somber music continues]

201
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:16,610
I love you so much, Brother.

202
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:20,698
I love you so much, Brother. [sobs]

203
00:12:23,784 --> 00:12:28,414
[sniffling, sobbing quietly]

204
00:12:32,751 --> 00:12:34,295
[music fades]

205
00:12:35,212 --> 00:12:36,338
[Scott exhales heavily]

206
00:12:37,465 --> 00:12:39,175
I can't believe that after all that…

207
00:12:41,135 --> 00:12:42,094
it was him.

208
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:43,637
Your uncle.

209
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:46,599
[Alice] At first, [sighs]

210
00:12:46,682 --> 00:12:49,059
when I would think
about my dad's final days…

211
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:52,438
it would make me feel so sad.

212
00:12:53,689 --> 00:12:55,232
[sniffles]

213
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:56,859
Right before his death…

214
00:12:57,818 --> 00:13:00,404
he found out what that man did to me.

215
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:03,532
It pains me so much to think that,

216
00:13:03,616 --> 00:13:06,160
[breathes heavily] he carried that weight…

217
00:13:07,077 --> 00:13:08,662
all on his own.

218
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:12,416
But he never showed it to me.

219
00:13:13,834 --> 00:13:16,337
[Alice] <i>He was still smiling at me…</i>

220
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:18,547
<i>comforting me…</i>

221
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:21,217
<i>inviting me out for milkshakes…</i>

222
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:22,968
<i>like nothing happened.</i>

223
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:25,179
[melancholic music playing]

224
00:13:25,262 --> 00:13:26,847
[sobs] But…

225
00:13:28,807 --> 00:13:31,060
what I'm just thinking now is…

226
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:33,562
that my dad's last moment…

227
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:36,273
<i>was spent protecting me.</i>

228
00:13:39,693 --> 00:13:41,904
That was the truth of his life.

229
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:45,449
Love, not pain.

230
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:48,327
That gives me peace.

231
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:51,205
[melancholic music continues]

232
00:13:51,288 --> 00:13:52,831
And I'm so grateful,

233
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:55,918
that I had such a great dad…

234
00:13:56,585 --> 00:13:58,128
even just for a little while.

235
00:13:58,212 --> 00:14:03,092
[melancholic music continues]

236
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:04,718
[Alice sniffles]

237
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:06,512
You did the same thing for Seth.

238
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,598
Even with all that you are carrying,

239
00:14:10,307 --> 00:14:12,059
you still protected him through all of it.

240
00:14:12,142 --> 00:14:13,143
[inhales]

241
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:15,479
You love fiercely, Alice…

242
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:18,274
…just like your dad.

243
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,068
And I'm grateful for you.

244
00:14:21,735 --> 00:14:22,653
[sobs]

245
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:23,863
Every day.

246
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:27,825
[sniffles]

247
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:34,206
- [crying, sobbing]
- [melancholic music continues]

248
00:14:37,751 --> 00:14:39,128
[music fades]

249
00:14:41,922 --> 00:14:43,007
- [Tim] Wow!
- [Tom] Alright.

250
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:45,342
Brands are lining up
with offers to work with you.

251
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:46,093
[Mel chuckles]

252
00:14:46,176 --> 00:14:49,805
Actually, even TV guesting's,
everyone wants you.

253
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,223
And…

254
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:53,183
Where were they a few months ago?

255
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:55,060
[Tom mouth clicks]
You know how people are!

256
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:59,023
They love a villain with a redemption arc.

257
00:14:59,106 --> 00:15:00,190
[Mel chuckles]

258
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:01,859
I'm fine with everything, okay?

259
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:04,403
You guys handle it. But,

260
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:08,198
the only schedule that cannot be moved
is the fashion show for SINTA.

261
00:15:08,574 --> 00:15:10,117
It's very important.

262
00:15:10,659 --> 00:15:13,078
The show will raise
funds for the organization

263
00:15:13,162 --> 00:15:16,916
and of course, help more women like me.

264
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:22,796
And I'm so excited
to style the survivors on the runway.

265
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,256
[mouth clicks] Imagine, after everything

266
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:26,467
they've been through
with domestic violence,

267
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:30,387
I want these women
to feel beautiful and powerful.

268
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:32,097
And they will, okay?

269
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:34,391
But can we talk about--

270
00:15:34,475 --> 00:15:35,601
Oops, wait!

271
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,187
Those people are going to have to wait.

272
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,980
My friends are waiting for me,

273
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:43,442
and right now,
my friends are my number one priority.

274
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:45,194
Ouch…

275
00:15:45,986 --> 00:15:47,488
What about us?

276
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:48,906
Oh, come on! [laughs]

277
00:15:48,989 --> 00:15:51,325
Of course you guys
are important to me too.

278
00:15:51,408 --> 00:15:53,702
- You're sulking already!
- [chuckles]

279
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:56,330
- But seriously, thank you.
- [mellow music playing]

280
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:57,831
- Hmm!
- Hmm!

281
00:15:57,915 --> 00:15:59,750
Thank you for sticking with me.

282
00:16:00,417 --> 00:16:01,877
I'm very, very grateful.

283
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:05,464
I really appreciate you two. [chuckles]

284
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:07,132
Wow, you're so good at sweet-talking!

285
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:09,843
- Exactly!
- Sweet-talking?

286
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:11,804
- That's not sweet-talking, okay!
- Come here.

287
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:12,930
[chuckles]

288
00:16:13,013 --> 00:16:14,431
- You're really such a crybaby.
- I know!

289
00:16:14,515 --> 00:16:16,308
[chuckling]

290
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:17,977
We're so happy for you, Mel.

291
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:20,437
- I'm so happy too.
- We're always here for you.

292
00:16:20,521 --> 00:16:21,772
- Okay?
- I know.

293
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:23,315
- Keep fighting!
- [chuckling]

294
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:24,274
You're so silly.

295
00:16:24,358 --> 00:16:27,027
- [chuckling]
- [mellow music continues]

296
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:28,153
[car door closes]

297
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:31,365
What if we shoot
here in the cemetery, dear?

298
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:33,367
What do you think? Would it fit?

299
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:34,618
You're right, Ma!

300
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:36,870
- It's perfect for creepy vibes.
- Hmm.

301
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:41,041
I'll just draft
the script and show it to you

302
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:43,335
so we can shoot before we go home.

303
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:45,004
- [chuckles]
- Right now?

304
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:47,423
Dear, can't we just do it tomorrow? Hmm?

305
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:50,551
Pa, we have a scheduled episode drop.

306
00:16:50,634 --> 00:16:52,177
- It can't be delayed.
- Oh!

307
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:54,555
You're going to be in
trouble with my producer!

308
00:16:54,638 --> 00:16:57,266
Look, love, we already have a draft. Look.

309
00:16:57,683 --> 00:16:58,600
Let me see!

310
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:03,147
[Chloe] <i>29 years ago,</i>
<i>August 16, 1996 to be exact,</i>

311
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:06,150
<i>an 11-year-old girl ran away from home,</i>

312
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:09,319
<i>and she had a deep reason for doing so.</i>

313
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:11,697
<i>A woman helped the child</i>

314
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:15,367
<i>and immediately brought</i>
<i>her to the Pasay City NLEA police station.</i>

315
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:19,288
<i>That was when everyone found</i>
<i>out this was not just an ordinary case.</i>

316
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:21,915
<i>This will surely shock you.</i>

317
00:17:22,458 --> 00:17:24,460
So, is it okay? How was I there?

318
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:27,463
Uh, love,
maybe tone your voice down a bit.

319
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:29,423
- You sounded like a scary teacher--
- [smack]

320
00:17:29,506 --> 00:17:30,591
- Ouch! Just kidding!
- [chuckles]

321
00:17:30,674 --> 00:17:31,884
- Love, I was just kidding!
- ["Sabay Sabay Tayo" playing]

322
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:33,177
You were really good, promise!

323
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:34,428
You don't even seem like a newbie.

324
00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:36,472
You're so good, you could be an actress!

325
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:37,639
- [chuckles]
- Oh…

326
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:38,974
[chuckling]

327
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:40,184
You, dear, what do you think?

328
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:42,519
Ma, I already told you,

329
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:44,188
you're really, really good at that!

330
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:47,066
It's giving seasoned
broadcast journalist vibes.

331
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:49,735
- Wow!
- It's giving Karen Davila!

332
00:17:49,818 --> 00:17:51,320
- [laughs]
- Really?

333
00:17:51,403 --> 00:17:53,363
But of course, dear, I want your approval.

334
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:55,532
I want you to be proud of me again.

335
00:17:55,616 --> 00:17:57,910
I want to bring back
the admiration you used to have for me.

336
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:03,415
[sighs] Ma,
my admiration for you never went away.

337
00:18:03,999 --> 00:18:05,667
It just changed.

338
00:18:06,585 --> 00:18:11,423
I learned that I shouldn't
idolize people too much.

339
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:13,133
Even you, my own mother.

340
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:16,470
Because everyone has flaws.

341
00:18:16,553 --> 00:18:17,679
Everyone makes mistakes.

342
00:18:18,305 --> 00:18:19,973
[sighs] They're only human.

343
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:23,560
But even so, Ma, people can still change,

344
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:25,145
- Hmm.
- if they really want to,

345
00:18:25,229 --> 00:18:26,355
and if they put in the effort.

346
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:27,689
- [chuckles]
- Hmm!

347
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:29,358
- [smooches]
- [chuckling]

348
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:31,860
- My daughter is really so smart!
- [chuckles]

349
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:34,029
You know, dear,
that's exactly what I'm doing now,

350
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:35,781
trying to become a better person.

351
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:37,908
[sighs] You're doing a good job, Ma!

352
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:40,369
Your character development is amazing!

353
00:18:40,452 --> 00:18:41,870
- Really?
- [laughing]

354
00:18:41,954 --> 00:18:46,959
My ears are thankful
because of this new version, Beth 2.0!

355
00:18:47,042 --> 00:18:48,001
- So annoying!
- Ouch!

356
00:18:48,085 --> 00:18:49,586
- Just kidding, love.
- You're always like that!

357
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:52,089
Love, your aura is different now.
You look so beautiful.

358
00:18:52,172 --> 00:18:53,048
- [chuckles]
- Of course!

359
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,341
You look so kind.

360
00:18:54,424 --> 00:18:56,135
- I've changed my life.
- [gushes, chuckles]

361
00:18:56,218 --> 00:18:57,845
Oh, there's Erica.

362
00:18:57,928 --> 00:18:59,763
- Wait, you go ahead.
- Oh, alright.

363
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:00,806
- I'll just wait for Erica.
- Okay, Ma.

364
00:19:00,889 --> 00:19:02,141
- Come on, dear.
- Alright.

365
00:19:02,224 --> 00:19:03,350
[Beth] Erica.

366
00:19:05,352 --> 00:19:06,728
[Erica chuckles]

367
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:08,147
- [smooches]
- [music fades]

368
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:16,029
Can we talk?

369
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:21,034
[Erica] You're leaving?

370
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:23,412
I'm going on a backpacking tour in Europe.

371
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:25,664
That was Steve's and my plan.

372
00:19:27,332 --> 00:19:28,792
Maybe while I'm doing that,

373
00:19:28,876 --> 00:19:31,295
my mind will become
clearer about what I should do next.

374
00:19:34,798 --> 00:19:36,258
Do you regret,

375
00:19:37,259 --> 00:19:41,763
that you had to shoot
your brother just to save me?

376
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:47,394
No.

377
00:19:47,477 --> 00:19:49,271
[pensive music playing]

378
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:53,692
But I would be lying if I said
I wasn't affected by what happened.

379
00:19:55,360 --> 00:20:00,532
I wish it hadn't come
to the point where I had to shoot him.

380
00:20:02,534 --> 00:20:06,705
That I reached the point where
I had to make that kind of decision.

381
00:20:08,790 --> 00:20:10,709
But if I hadn't done it,

382
00:20:10,792 --> 00:20:13,086
I wouldn't have
been able to forgive myself.

383
00:20:15,130 --> 00:20:17,299
It would have felt
like I failed Edong too.

384
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:20,677
I saved you,

385
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:24,640
but I also believe I saved Edong in a way.

386
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:29,519
[pensive music continues]

387
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:32,272
But that doesn't mean
everything will become easy.

388
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,108
No.

389
00:20:36,276 --> 00:20:37,569
It won't be easy.

390
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:40,113
[sniffles, inhales deeply]

391
00:20:40,781 --> 00:20:43,325
I know that when you see me, it's hard.

392
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:46,370
You remember what you did.

393
00:20:47,329 --> 00:20:48,872
The decision you made.

394
00:20:48,956 --> 00:20:53,418
[pensive music continues]

395
00:20:53,502 --> 00:20:55,796
You know, when you told me

396
00:20:56,171 --> 00:20:58,423
that you were the one
who gave me 50 pesos,

397
00:20:58,882 --> 00:21:00,592
when I had nothing,

398
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:02,970
when I was at my lowest.

399
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:08,558
I thought, maybe our lives were connected.

400
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:12,145
[pensive music continues]

401
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:13,230
[Erica] <i>Destiny.</i>

402
00:21:14,189 --> 00:21:15,065
<i>Fate.</i>

403
00:21:16,024 --> 00:21:17,192
<i>Invisible string.</i>

404
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:19,736
<i>Whatever you want to call it.</i>

405
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:25,659
But now, I feel like…

406
00:21:26,952 --> 00:21:28,745
it's not a string at all, Lucas.

407
00:21:30,789 --> 00:21:32,332
It feels like shackles.

408
00:21:34,209 --> 00:21:35,752
Like heavy chains.

409
00:21:37,296 --> 00:21:39,131
And we're tired of dragging them along.

410
00:21:43,927 --> 00:21:45,262
So maybe…

411
00:21:49,099 --> 00:21:50,392
it's time to let go.

412
00:21:50,475 --> 00:21:55,439
[pensive music continues]

413
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:03,572
In another life…

414
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:08,076
If all this didn't happen,

415
00:22:10,579 --> 00:22:12,331
if Louisa wasn't murdered,

416
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:16,126
if all those things
didn't happen to Edong.

417
00:22:19,296 --> 00:22:21,048
maybe we're still together.

418
00:22:24,217 --> 00:22:25,927
[Lucas] <i>Holding hands,</i>

419
00:22:26,386 --> 00:22:28,180
<i>leaving Amurao,</i>

420
00:22:29,264 --> 00:22:30,849
<i>to build a brand new life.</i>

421
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:33,310
<i>A happy one.</i>

422
00:22:35,812 --> 00:22:36,855
Together.

423
00:22:40,025 --> 00:22:41,109
[sniffles]

424
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:42,277
Maybe.

425
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:43,487
[Lucas sniffles]

426
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:47,949
[pensive music continues]

427
00:22:51,119 --> 00:22:52,537
[music fades]

428
00:22:52,621 --> 00:22:54,915
Why don't you
confess your feelings to her again?

429
00:22:56,666 --> 00:22:57,959
She isn't ready.

430
00:22:59,169 --> 00:23:02,047
She still has a lot to deal with,

431
00:23:02,464 --> 00:23:04,132
to fix, to think about.

432
00:23:06,176 --> 00:23:07,969
But you're still willing to wait?

433
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:10,263
[chuckles]

434
00:23:10,347 --> 00:23:13,433
How will she change
her mind if you don't help her out?

435
00:23:13,934 --> 00:23:15,352
You know what?

436
00:23:15,769 --> 00:23:19,689
I realized late that I liked Ryan
because he didn't give up on me.

437
00:23:20,857 --> 00:23:22,192
I don't need that.

438
00:23:22,692 --> 00:23:24,653
She'll realize soon enough

439
00:23:25,028 --> 00:23:26,780
that I'm the right man for her.

440
00:23:26,863 --> 00:23:28,323
[scoffs] Oh, wow.

441
00:23:28,406 --> 00:23:31,076
I like that confidence.

442
00:23:31,159 --> 00:23:32,244
High five.

443
00:23:33,203 --> 00:23:34,871
Yeah. Keep it up.

444
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:36,706
[light-hearted music playing]

445
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:37,916
But Erica…

446
00:23:38,834 --> 00:23:41,169
I don't think this is our ending.

447
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:45,132
We'll see each other again.

448
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:52,264
I don't think fate is so cruel
that it won't give us some light

449
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:55,016
after all this
darkness we've gone through.

450
00:23:55,100 --> 00:24:00,147
[light-hearted music continues]

451
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:01,189
You're right.

452
00:24:03,608 --> 00:24:04,860
We'll meet again.

453
00:24:09,906 --> 00:24:11,283
Happy birthday.

454
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:25,797
[light-hearted music continues]

455
00:24:32,053 --> 00:24:33,930
[both sniffling]

456
00:24:34,014 --> 00:24:35,265
You know,

457
00:24:35,348 --> 00:24:37,267
this is my birthday food.

458
00:24:37,809 --> 00:24:41,396
I never celebrated
my birthday with a cake.

459
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:43,773
I would always get these.

460
00:24:46,526 --> 00:24:47,527
Thank you.

461
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:52,657
[light-hearted music swells]

462
00:25:10,217 --> 00:25:12,177
Take care of yourself, Lucas.

463
00:25:29,569 --> 00:25:35,784
[light-hearted music continues]

464
00:25:42,958 --> 00:25:44,584
[music fades]

465
00:25:49,172 --> 00:25:50,465
[exhales]

466
00:25:55,345 --> 00:25:56,763
If you think about it,

467
00:25:57,889 --> 00:25:59,516
if it wasn't for Edong,

468
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:03,645
we wouldn't have found out
the secrets we're hiding from each other.

469
00:26:03,728 --> 00:26:06,398
[pensive music playing]

470
00:26:06,481 --> 00:26:10,777
I wouldn't be able to share what
was going through with my nightmares.

471
00:26:12,445 --> 00:26:14,948
Mel wouldn't be able
to talk about Anton's abuse.

472
00:26:15,615 --> 00:26:17,617
Beth, your guilt.

473
00:26:19,035 --> 00:26:20,787
And Erica,

474
00:26:21,371 --> 00:26:24,582
if Edong didn't force
you to come back to Amurao,

475
00:26:25,458 --> 00:26:28,753
you wouldn't know
the truth about your mom.

476
00:26:28,837 --> 00:26:30,672
[somber music continues]

477
00:26:30,755 --> 00:26:34,050
We may never know
what really happened to Louisa.

478
00:26:35,468 --> 00:26:38,555
But today, on her death anniversary,

479
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:40,682
we can say that,

480
00:26:41,349 --> 00:26:44,227
we've given her the justice she deserves.

481
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:47,772
And Edong…

482
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:52,652
he will never be a complete villain to me.

483
00:26:56,448 --> 00:26:58,325
He'll be in my mind,

484
00:26:59,075 --> 00:27:00,160
forever.

485
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:06,041
But, even though I'm enlightened

486
00:27:06,124 --> 00:27:08,835
and living my truth, as Chloe says it,

487
00:27:09,669 --> 00:27:11,963
I still wouldn't want
that to happen again.

488
00:27:12,464 --> 00:27:13,882
- Over my sexy body.
- ["Sabay Sabay Tayo" playing]

489
00:27:13,965 --> 00:27:15,842
[all giggle]

490
00:27:15,925 --> 00:27:18,136
Yeah, please. No repeat.

491
00:27:18,219 --> 00:27:19,304
Never again.

492
00:27:21,264 --> 00:27:24,517
[exhales] I'm just so glad
the four of us survived that.

493
00:27:25,268 --> 00:27:29,189
Except for Mel, who's late again!

494
00:27:29,606 --> 00:27:31,441
[sighs] But it's true.

495
00:27:31,524 --> 00:27:33,360
I love you guys.

496
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:35,362
I love you, Erica.

497
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:37,614
[giggling]

498
00:27:37,697 --> 00:27:40,533
Aww… they're good now.

499
00:27:40,617 --> 00:27:42,369
[giggling]

500
00:27:43,411 --> 00:27:44,371
And!

501
00:27:45,205 --> 00:27:48,333
- Happy birthday, Erica!
- Happy birthday!

502
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,418
- Happy birthday!
- Happy birthday!

503
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:52,545
- Happy birthday, Aunt Erica.
- Wow.

504
00:27:52,629 --> 00:27:55,215
- You got me a gift.
- Happy birthday.

505
00:27:56,341 --> 00:27:58,885
Guys, you know
I don't celebrate my birthday.

506
00:27:58,968 --> 00:28:00,345
- Mhm-hmm.
- [Erica] Because…

507
00:28:00,428 --> 00:28:02,263
this is Louisa's death anniversary.

508
00:28:02,347 --> 00:28:04,641
From now on, that is gonna change.

509
00:28:05,141 --> 00:28:08,353
- We'll celebrate it all the time!
- Mhm-hmm.

510
00:28:08,436 --> 00:28:09,562
[Annette] Yes!

511
00:28:12,357 --> 00:28:14,609
We've prepared
something for you at the house.

512
00:28:14,692 --> 00:28:19,447
[tender music playing]

513
00:28:29,499 --> 00:28:32,419
And your sister
won't take no for an answer!

514
00:28:32,502 --> 00:28:38,383
[tender music continues]

515
00:28:38,466 --> 00:28:40,093
So, that's your sense of humor, huh?

516
00:28:42,971 --> 00:28:44,305
[Althea] Don't worry, Erica.

517
00:28:44,764 --> 00:28:46,850
You'll get to know more,

518
00:28:46,933 --> 00:28:48,810
amazing things about me.

519
00:28:50,311 --> 00:28:53,106
I survived death, Erica…

520
00:28:53,189 --> 00:28:56,151
just to be with you on your birthday.

521
00:28:56,234 --> 00:29:00,572
[tender music continues]

522
00:29:02,031 --> 00:29:03,116
[sniffles]

523
00:29:07,454 --> 00:29:09,414
[Annette] Oh gosh!
Let's leave that for later!

524
00:29:09,789 --> 00:29:11,708
Come on, let's celebrate.

525
00:29:11,791 --> 00:29:14,836
[Annette] That's why I came here,
so none of you disappear.

526
00:29:14,919 --> 00:29:16,379
[Alice] Let's go!

527
00:29:16,463 --> 00:29:18,131
Happy birthday, Erica.

528
00:29:19,424 --> 00:29:22,177
- [Annette laughing]
- [tender music continues]

529
00:29:22,260 --> 00:29:24,012
Erica? Let's go!

530
00:29:24,095 --> 00:29:25,764
- [Alice] Let's go.
- Alright.

531
00:29:25,847 --> 00:29:27,682
- Let's go.
- [Alice] Let's go!

532
00:29:27,766 --> 00:29:30,685
[Beth singing "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]

533
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:34,189
[Alice singing "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]

534
00:29:41,946 --> 00:29:44,073
[Beth laughs]
I don't know the lyrics anymore!

535
00:29:44,157 --> 00:29:49,412
[continues singing "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]

536
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:54,250
[Erica] You know
what I've always thought about

537
00:29:54,334 --> 00:29:56,211
what if all that never happened?

538
00:29:57,086 --> 00:29:58,880
What if Louisa never died?

539
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:01,424
Where do you think we would be today?

540
00:30:01,758 --> 00:30:02,884
You know what?

541
00:30:03,468 --> 00:30:05,470
I think you still
would have become a lawyer.

542
00:30:06,346 --> 00:30:08,848
You don't need tragedy
to be who you are meant to be.

543
00:30:08,932 --> 00:30:12,101
- [poignant music playing]
- [Erica chuckles softly]

544
00:30:12,185 --> 00:30:13,311
[Mel sighs]

545
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:17,649
But you know, that night…

546
00:30:18,525 --> 00:30:19,776
what happened to Louisa…

547
00:30:20,819 --> 00:30:22,195
it will always connect us.

548
00:30:23,363 --> 00:30:24,405
But…

549
00:30:24,989 --> 00:30:28,660
I hope this time,
the connection, should be our choice.

550
00:30:29,786 --> 00:30:31,079
It should be us.

551
00:30:32,163 --> 00:30:33,248
our friendship.

552
00:30:33,748 --> 00:30:34,916
[chuckles softly]

553
00:30:34,999 --> 00:30:37,460
I hope after
everything we've been through,

554
00:30:37,544 --> 00:30:39,504
we could all be friends, right?

555
00:30:39,587 --> 00:30:42,507
Absolutely! I have so many
things to make up to you guys!

556
00:30:43,007 --> 00:30:44,384
Especially on you, Erica.

557
00:30:44,968 --> 00:30:47,136
- [Mel] Look at you!
- [laughs]

558
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:49,180
Speaking of making amends…

559
00:30:49,264 --> 00:30:52,016
Alice, you're staying here
for another month, right?

560
00:30:52,100 --> 00:30:53,226
Yes.

561
00:30:53,893 --> 00:30:57,188
So my family, Seth and Scott,
can have a little vacation.

562
00:30:57,272 --> 00:30:59,065
- A real vacation this time.
- Mmm-hmm.

563
00:30:59,148 --> 00:31:01,818
- But, make sure to make time for us, okay.
- Yeah, she's right!

564
00:31:01,901 --> 00:31:04,988
You might hide from us again,
like a killer is chasing us!

565
00:31:05,071 --> 00:31:06,072
[giggles]

566
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:09,617
Wait, what about the big house?

567
00:31:09,993 --> 00:31:11,494
What will happen to that?

568
00:31:12,161 --> 00:31:13,204
We'll sell it.

569
00:31:13,288 --> 00:31:14,914
[poignant music swells]

570
00:31:14,998 --> 00:31:18,543
Maybe someone else can
make happy memories there.

571
00:31:19,210 --> 00:31:20,420
But for us,

572
00:31:20,503 --> 00:31:22,797
- It's no longer possible.
- [chuckles]

573
00:31:22,881 --> 00:31:24,799
- Not in this lifetime.
- [Beth scoffs]

574
00:31:25,675 --> 00:31:28,052
Never again. Hello!

575
00:31:28,136 --> 00:31:30,889
[laughter]

576
00:31:31,723 --> 00:31:32,932
Finally.

577
00:31:33,975 --> 00:31:35,476
The truth set us free.

578
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:40,440
[poignant music continues]

579
00:32:03,004 --> 00:32:04,380
[music fades]

580
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:12,347
[eerie whistling "Sabay Sabay Tayo]

581
00:32:23,566 --> 00:32:27,946
- [eerie music playing
- [whistling continues]

582
00:32:40,166 --> 00:32:45,797
[music becomes suspenseful]

583
00:34:25,354 --> 00:34:27,940
[music crescendos]

584
00:34:29,025 --> 00:34:31,778
[crickets chirping]

585
00:34:31,861 --> 00:34:37,325
[foreboding music playing]

586
00:34:40,078 --> 00:34:47,085
[sinister whistling "Sabay Sabay Tayo"]
